article.description: Pat Andree had 22 points as Lehigh rolled past Navy 83-57 on Saturday.
article.headline: Andree scores 22 to lift Lehigh over Navy 83-57
article.linkText: Andree scores 22 to lift Lehigh over Navy 83-57
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- Pat Andree had 22 points as Lehigh rolled past Navy 83-57 on Saturday. Andree made 5 of 7 3-pointers. He added seven rebounds. Lance Tejada had 17 points for Lehigh (16-7, 9-3 Patriot League). Kyle Leufroy added 10 points. James Karnik had nine rebounds for the home team. The Midshipmen's 27.9 field goal percentage represented the worst mark by a Lehigh opponent this season. Hasan Abdullah had 14 points and seven rebounds for the Midshipmen (8-15, 5-7). Josiah Strong added 10 points. George Kiernan scored only 2 points despite entering the contest as the Midshipmen's leading scorer at 13 points per game. He failed to make a shot from beyond the arc (0 of 6). The Mountain Hawks improve to 2-0 against the Midshipmen for the season. Lehigh defeated Navy 85-74 on Jan. 23. Lehigh plays Bucknell on the road on Monday. Navy plays Lafayette at home on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
